message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The first interdigital space and hallux are innervated by the deep peroneal nerve, so paresthesias and a hallux valgus deformity suggest compression of this nerve. The other options do not innervate this area.

Compression of this nerve can cause painful paresthesias in the foot. The other options do not typically innervate this area of the foot.

We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The hallux valgus deformity is associated with compression of the deep peroneal nerve, which innervates the first interdigital space. Superficial peroneal nerve innervates the lateral side of the foot, sural nerve innervates the lateral aspect of the foot, and medial plantar nerve innervates the medial aspect of the foot.
